# Cursor Rules for SvelteKit-NestJS-Turbo

## Project Context

This is a production-ready full-stack SvelteKit-NestJS-Turbo with:
- Frontend: SvelteKit + TailwindCSS + Shadcn-Svelte + Melt UI
- Backend: NestJS + TypeORM + PostgreSQL
- Monorepo: Turborepo
- Database: PostgreSQL 16 + Redis 7

## File Structure

```
apps/
  web/          # SvelteKit frontend (port 3002)
  api/          # NestJS backend (port 3001)
packages/
  types/        # Shared TypeScript types
  config/       # ESLint & Prettier configs
  ui/           # Shared UI components (reserved)
  database/     # Shared entities (reserved)
```

## Development Commands

```bash
# Start all services
npm run dev

# Start individual apps
npm run dev --workspace=web
npm run dev --workspace=api

# Build all
npm run build

# Database
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d  # Start PostgreSQL + Redis
```

## Code Style Guidelines

### TypeScript
- Use strict mode
- Prefer `const` over `let`
- Use async/await over Promises
- Keep functions small (<50 lines)

### Naming
- Files: `kebab-case.ts`
- Components: `PascalCase.svelte`
- Functions: `camelCase()`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

### Svelte Components
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  // 1. Imports
  import { onMount } from 'svelte';
  
  // 2. Props
  export let title: string;
  
  // 3. State
  let count = 0;
  
  // 4. Reactive statements
  $: doubled = count * 2;
  
  // 5. Functions
  function increment() { count += 1; }
  
  // 6. Lifecycle
  onMount(() => {});
</script>

<!-- Markup with TailwindCSS -->
<div class="flex items-center gap-4">
  <h1>{title}</h1>
  <button on:click={increment}>+</button>
</div>
```

### NestJS
- Use decorators consistently
- Implement DTOs with class-validator
- Add Swagger decorators for all endpoints
- Use proper dependency injection

## Adding Features

### New API Endpoint
```bash
cd apps/api
npx nest g module modules/users
npx nest g controller modules/users
npx nest g service modules/users
```

### New Frontend Route
```bash
# Create in apps/web/src/routes/
touch apps/web/src/routes/about/+page.svelte
```

### Shared Types
Add to `packages/types/index.ts` and use in both apps.

## Database

- PostgreSQL: `localhost:5433`
- Redis: `localhost:6379`
- Connection config: `apps/api/.env`

## Testing

- Unit tests: Vitest (setup ready)
- E2E tests: Playwright (setup ready)

## Styling

- Use TailwindCSS utility classes first
- Use `cn()` helper from `$lib/utils` for conditional classes
- Extend theme in `tailwind.config.js`

## Component Libraries

- **Shadcn-Svelte**: Copy-paste components from https://shadcn-svelte.com
- **Melt UI**: Headless primitives from https://melt-ui.com

## Security

- Validate all inputs (class-validator)
- Use parameterized queries (TypeORM does this)
- Sanitize error messages in production
- Keep secrets in `.env` (never commit)

## Performance

- Code split routes automatically (SvelteKit)
- Use database indexes
- Implement caching with Redis
- Use pagination for large datasets

## When Adding Code

1. Read existing patterns first
2. Match project style
3. Add TypeScript types
4. Test locally before committing
5. Update README if adding new features

## Common Patterns

### API Response Format
```typescript
interface ApiResponse<T = any> {
  success: boolean;
  data?: T;
  error?: string;
  message?: string;
}
```

### Error Handling
```typescript
try {
  // code
} catch (error) {
  this.logger.error('Context', error);
  throw new InternalServerErrorException('User-friendly message');
}
```

### Component Props
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import type { User } from '@repo/types';
  export let user: User;
  export let onUpdate: (user: User) => void = () => {};
</script>
```

## Avoid

- Don't use `any` type
- Don't commit secrets
- Don't use `rm` (use `trash` if available)
- Don't modify config without checking existing setup
- Don't add dependencies without checking alternatives

## Goals

- Keep it simple
- Maintain type safety
- Follow existing patterns
- Write self-documenting code
- Prioritize developer experience
